HEADWORD: Yoncopin
<hw>Yon"co*pin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Perhaps corrupted
from Illinois <ets>micoupena</ets>, Chippewa <ets>makopin</ets>, the
American lotus.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A local name in parts of
the Mississippi Valley for the American lotus (<spn>Nelumbo
lutea</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yond</ent>⟦br⟧
